-- MOVES-UBS's UK head to leave bank at end of September
-- By Clare Hutchison
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 12:35PM EDT
-- None



LONDON, July 31 (Reuters) - The chief executive of UBS's <UBSN.VX> British operations is to leave the Swiss bank at the end of September, according to an internal memo seen by Reuters on Thursday.

Mark Yallop, who joined the bank in 2013, is stepping down to pursue other business interests, the memo said. Details of his next role were not disclosed. During his time at UBS Yallop oversaw the restructuring of the UK business, reviewing its governance, risk and control arrangements and was responsible for strengthening its relationships with regulatory bodies.